article.headline: Florida International 71, Louisiana-Lafayette 68
article.story: MIAMI (AP) -- Michael James scored 16 points to lead Florida International to a 71-68 win over Louisiana-Lafayette on Thursday. Louisiana-Lafayette (9-19, 7-10 Sun Belt Conference) took a one point lead into the half, but Florida International (12-15, 7-10) came back in the second period for the close victory. Florida International's Chris Fuller scored 15 points and Johwen Villegas scored 13. Besides being Louisiana-Lafayette's top scorer with 20 points, Elijah Millsap also had 14 rebounds. Ross Mouton scored 18 points, and David Dees added 12. The final score was close, but Louisiana-Lafayette actually held a 10-point lead at one point during the first half. Florida International's largest lead was 6 points in the second half.
